race.comment: MACEDON ROSE (16) is in a top metro stable and is clearly the one to beat. Didn't have much luck at Ballarat last time as a short-priced favourite and is still well shy of her best recorded at Stakes level. A top hoop rides. HANDY FRIEND (1) resumed with a narrow defeat at Kyneton and is further improved. Has an awkward gate to contend with but fitter should be right in the finish. MATERAZZI (9) was vet cleared after a plain run at Caulfield at 70 level. He was an easy Maiden winner prior and maps for a soft run. Worth a look at the each-way odds. Ditto KISS MY ROCK (2) who resumed in solid order. Has plenty up the sleeve and the mile is ideal for for him.
